Police in the Eastern Cape on Monday said officers were investigating a double murder case after two women were killed in their vehicle in Ntibaneni locality in the Eastern Cape on Sunday night.
“It is alleged that two women were driving a double cab with a CA registration passing Ntibaneni locality at about 21:00. According to an eyewitness they saw the vehicle passing followed by an Avanza and afterwards they heard some shots fired,” a statement from the police said.
“Police were summoned to the shooting scene and on arrival they found two women with bullet wounds fatally struck.”
Police were appealing for anyone with information on the shooting incident to come forward or contact them on 08600 10111.
– African News Agency (ANA)